    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: TRW/ROSS-TAS 40, 55, 65 AND 85 - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0500308" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <para>Stop the vehicle with wheels pointed straight ahead.</para>
        <para>Clean off all outside dirt from around the fittings and hose connections before you remove the gear.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block wheels of vehicle and apply parking brake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen bolt and remove pitman arm from output shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen pinch bolt and disconnect the steering column from the input shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect hydraulic line from pump to pressure port in steering gear. Plug this port.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect return line to steering gear return port. Plug this port.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove gear from frame.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
